The pair welcomed their first child together, as Pop Sugar reports. On Sunday (Sept. 13), while promoting his new film, Concrete Cowboy, at the Toronto International Film Festival, Elba confirmed that he and his wife are now parents to a baby boy. “So, it really resonates with me, I’m a father of two boys, and definitely I can’t wait for my youngest to see this film,” Idris said. Elba, 48, also has an 18-year-old daughter named Isan and a six-year-old son named Winston, from previous relationships. NEW YORK, NEW YORK – DECEMBER 16: Sabrina Dhowre Elba and Idris Elba attend the world premiere of “Cats” at Alice Tully Hall, Lincoln Center on December 16, 2019 in New York City. (Photo by Dia Dipasupil/Getty Images) Elba and Dhowre first began dating around March 2017, and Elba popped the question at a London screening of his film Yardie back in February 2018. A year later, the couple made things official by tying the knot in Morocco. Back in August, both Elba and Dhowre contracted COVID-19, as we previously reported. “At the time that we got sick, the media was pushing hard on how dangerous it was,’ Dhowre said. “At one point, Idris really thought that this could be the end,” she continued. “He has asthma. He is older. It was really scary.” The pair survived the virus, but it changed the couple’s perspectives. “That kind of unsureness about what’s coming next leaves you with a bit of anxiety,” she said. “But having been sick and being okay also now gives you this new lease on life.” Download the app to LISTEN LIVE wherever you are and connect with us like never before!'}]

'pageNumber': 0, 'inputText': "I met Aaron Hagar a few years back with my podcast, Skidmarks Show. My cohost Jeff Allen had Aaron come hang out with us at the world’s biggest car show in Las Vegas, SEMA, which is part of the reason why this interview starts with us talking about cars and racing. Aaron was just getting ready to take a car to SoCal for some seat time with friends. Aaron and I became pretty good friends over the years. So when we all got the bad news about Eddie passing, I figured I give him a shout to see how the Hagar’s are holding up. What I thought might be a 15 minute chat turned into an almost hour long catch up between friends, and a whole lot of behind the scenes from the Hagar era Van Halen days. There’s a whole lot if stuff you’ve never heard before in this interview. It was stuff I’ve never heard before either. But it was all eye witness, because Aaron was there. I turned the audio into a video so its more fun to watch. Some of the photos you’ll see are Aaron and I, some are from Aaron’s Facebook, and some are from those years when Van Halen was on top of the world. (We get into talking about Sammy, Van Halen, and Eddie around 13 minutes in, if you want to skip past the car talk.) Aaron is also an amazing artist in his own right and you should check out some of his stuff on his Facebook page. Plus he does custom special order work too, including turning your photos into a painting. And his photo realism is awesome.
